{
  "page": "Dragon dreams",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/5/58/Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg/300px-Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"220\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/5/58/Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg/450px-Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/5/58/Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg/600px-Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Fire_Made_Flesh_by_Jake_Murray.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>© Fantasy Flight Games</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/ea/Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg/300px-Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"464\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/ea/Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg/450px-Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/ea/Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg/600px-Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Game_of_thrones_covers_by_underdogmike-d4qkkhk.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>© Mike S Miller</div></div></div>\n<p>Prophetic dreams affect those with the <i>blood of the dragon</i>, who are known to have premonition-like dream ability - they are no ordinary dreams. They appear to involve <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a>.\n</p><p>No official term has been given for these specific dreams, but <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys</a> thinks of one of her recurring dreams as \"the <b>dragon dream</b>.\" Dragon dreams appear to have haunted those with the blood of the dragon throughout the generations; some more than others. \n</p><p>Members of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">House Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/House_Blackfyre\" title=\"House Blackfyre\">House Blackfyre</a> have had these dreams.  \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Cases\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Cases</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Daenys_the_Dreamer\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Daenys the Dreamer</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Aegon_the_Conqueror\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aegon the Conqueror</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Daeron_the_Drunken\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Daeron the Drunken</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Daemon_II_Blackfyre\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Daemon II Blackfyre</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Aerion_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aerion Targaryen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Aegon_V_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.6</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Aegon V Targaryen</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Maester_Aemon\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.7</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Maester Aemon</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Daenerys_Targaryen\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.8</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Daenerys Targaryen</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-11\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Cases\">Cases</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Cases\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Daenys_the_Dreamer\">Daenys the Dreamer</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Daenys the Dreamer\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Daenys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenys Targaryen\">Daenys Targaryen</a> was still a <a href=\"/index.php/Maiden\" title=\"Maiden\">maiden</a>,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> she had visions, including a powerful prophetic dream that <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> would be destroyed. <a href=\"/index.php/Aenar_Targaryen\" title=\"Aenar Targaryen\">Her father</a> had enough faith in her prophetic abilities to relocate his family to <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>. Valyria and all the other dragonlords were <a href=\"/index.php/Doom_of_Valyria\" title=\"Doom of Valyria\">destroyed</a> twelve years later.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aegon_the_Conqueror\">Aegon the Conqueror</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aegon the Conqueror\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>According to a semi-canon source, Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> had a dragon dream that contributed to his decision to conquer the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Daeron_the_Drunken\">Daeron the Drunken</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Daeron the Drunken\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Daeron_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Daeron Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Daeron Targaryen</a> told <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Dunk</a> about a dream he had. A great red <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> would fall on Ser Duncan, dead, but the <a href=\"/index.php/Knight\" title=\"Knight\">knight</a> would walk off alive. He said he did not know what it meant, but that his dreams came true and that he was scared of <a href=\"/index.php/Dunk\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dunk\">Dunk</a>. The dream turned out to be metaphorical, referring to the death of Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_Targaryen_(son_of_Daeron_II)\" title=\"Baelor Targaryen (son of Daeron II)\">Baelor Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a> mentions another dream of Daeron's:\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>\"I'm not stupid, ser. Someday the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a> will return. My brother Daeron's dreamed of it, and <a href=\"/index.php/Aerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aerys I Targaryen\">King Aerys</a> read it in a prophecy. Maybe it will be my <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon_egg\" title=\"Dragon egg\">egg</a> that hatches. That would be <i>splendid</i>.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Although Daeron's generally accepted cause of death was a pox caught from a whore, his maester<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> and younger brother Aemon attributed his death to his dreams.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Daemon_II_Blackfyre\">Daemon II Blackfyre</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Daemon II Blackfyre\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_II_Blackfyre\" title=\"Daemon II Blackfyre\">Daemon II Blackfyre</a>, in the guise of 'John the Fiddler', talks to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan</a>, saying that he recognized him on the road. Duncan had appeared to him in a dream in which Duncan wore the all-white armor of the <a href=\"/index.php/Kingsguard\" title=\"Kingsguard\">Kingsguard</a>. The Fiddler says his dreams always come true, as he dreamt <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aegon Blackfyre\">his</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Blackfyre\" title=\"Aemon Blackfyre\">brothers</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Redgrass_Field\" title=\"Battle of the Redgrass Field\">dead</a> once and also a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> hatching from an <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">egg</a> at <a href=\"/index.php/Whitewalls\" title=\"Whitewalls\">Whitewalls</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aerion_Targaryen\">Aerion Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aerion Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>According to Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a>, all three of his brothers dreamed of dragons and their dreams killed them.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Although the details of his dreams are unknown, Aemon's second eldest brother Aerion was consumed by a belief that he was a dragon in human form from a young age.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He famously drank <a href=\"/index.php/Wildfire\" title=\"Wildfire\">wildfire</a> under the belief it would transform him into a dragon, but it killed him instead.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Aegon_V_Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Aegon V Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The youngest of Aemon's brothers, King <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon V Targaryen</a>, also had dreams of dragons which eventually led to his death.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Like Aerion, the details of Aegon's dreams are unclear. According to <a href=\"/index.php/Maester\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Maester\">Maester</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Yandel\" title=\"Yandel\">Yandel</a> in his <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire_(Yandel)\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire (Yandel)\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, the king \"had come to dream of dragons flying once more above the Seven Kingdoms of Westeros,\" though Yandel may have used the word metaphorically. His final years were consumed by a search for ancient lore about dragon breeding in the hopes of bringing the dragons back, despite the misgivings of friends and counselors. This would culminate in an <a href=\"/index.php/Tragedy_at_Summerhall\" title=\"Tragedy at Summerhall\">attempt</a> to revive the dragons at <a href=\"/index.php/Summerhall\" title=\"Summerhall\">Summerhall</a> that went badly wrong, resulting in the deaths of Aegon and others.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Maester_Aemon\">Maester Aemon</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Maester Aemon\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Aemon_Targaryen_(son_of_Maekar_I)\" title=\"Aemon Targaryen (son of Maekar I)\">Aemon</a> tells <a href=\"/index.php/Samwell_Tarly\" title=\"Samwell Tarly\">Samwell Tarly</a>:\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I see them in my dreams, Sam.  I see a <a href=\"/index.php/Red_Comet\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Red Comet\">red star</a> bleeding in the sky.  I still remember red.  I see their shadows on the snow, hear the crack of leathern wings, feel their hot breath.  My brothers dreamed of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragons\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dragons\">dragons</a> too, and their dreams killed them, every one.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>As he weakens he spends more time sleeping. Sometimes he would call for Sam, insisting that he had to tell him something, but he would often forget what he meant to say by the time Sam arrived. Even when he did recall his talk was all a jumble.   He spoke of dreams and never named the dreamer, of a <a href=\"/index.php/Glass_candle\" title=\"Glass candle\">glass candle</a> that could not be lit and eggs that would not hatch.   He said the <a href=\"/index.php/Sphinx\" title=\"Sphinx\">sphinx</a> was the <a href=\"/index.php/Alleras\" title=\"Alleras\">riddle</a>, not the riddler. He asked Sam to read for him from a book by Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Barth\" title=\"Barth\">Barth</a>, whose writings had been burned during the reign of <a href=\"/index.php/Baelor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Baelor I Targaryen\">Baelor the Blessed</a>.   Once he woke up weeping, wailing:\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>the dragon must have three heads…but I am too old to be one of them.  I should be with <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">her</a>, showing her <a href=\"/index.php/The_way\" title=\"The way\">the way</a>, but my body has betrayed me.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>He mentions \"the prophecy\" and his \"brother’s dream\" to Sam - but does not mention what prophecy or which brother to Sam, or what the dream entailed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Daenerys_Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Daenerys Targaryen\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/2/2b/Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/300px-Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"383\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/2/2b/Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/450px-Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/2/2b/Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg/600px-Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragon_Dreamers_by_coldraindropsss.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Dragon dreamers Daenys, Aegon I, and Daenerys by coldraindropsss</div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> has dragon dreams preceding the birth of her three dragons. She dreams of a black <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> prior to her wedding day:<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys</a> was hitting her, hurting her. She was naked, clumsy with fear. She ran from him, but her body seemed thick and ungainly. He struck her again. She stumbled and fell. He struck her again. She stumbled and fell. “You woke the dragon,” he screamed as he kicked her. “You woke the dragon, you woke the dragon.” Her thighs were slick with blood. \nShe closed her eyes and whimpered. As if in answer, there was a hideous ripping sound and the crackling of some great fire. When she looked again <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys Targaryen\">Viserys</a> was gone, great columns of flame rose all around, and in the midst of them was the dragon. It turned its great head slowly. When its molten eyes found hers, she woke, shaking and covered with a fine sweat.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Newly wedded, when she is despairing in the <a href=\"/index.php/Dothraki_Sea\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Dothraki Sea\">Dothraki Sea</a>, and feeling that she cannot go on, she dreams of a black dragon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>There was only her and the dragon. Its scales were black as night, wet and slick with blood. Her blood, Dany sensed. Its eyes were pools of molten magma, and when it opened its mouth, the flame came roaring out in a hot jet.  She could hear it singing to her. She opened her arms to the fire, embraced it, let it swallow her whole, let it cleanse her cleanse her and temper her and scour her clean. She could feel her flesh sear and blacken and slough away, could feel her blood boil and turn to steam, and yet there was no pain. She felt strong and new and fierce.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<p>After the birth of her three dragons, <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> seems to no longer be dreaming of the black dragon, but she is plagued by other dreams and visions. \n</p><p>The night before the <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_Astapor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sack of Astapor\">sack of Astapor</a>, aboard the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Balerion_(ship)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Balerion (ship)\">Balerion</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/Daenerys_Targaryen\" title=\"Daenerys Targaryen\">Daenerys Targaryen</a> has what may be a prophetic dream that may involve the <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">Others</a>:\n</p>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>That night she dreamt she was <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaegar\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Rhaegar\">Rhaegar</a>, riding to the <a href=\"/index.php/Trident\" title=\"Trident\">Trident</a>. But she was mounted on a <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a>, not a horse.  When she saw the <a href=\"/index.php/Usurper\" title=\"Usurper\">Usurper</a>’s rebel host across the river <a href=\"/index.php/Others\" title=\"Others\">they were armored all in ice</a>, but she bathed them in dragonfire and they melted away like dew and turned the Trident into a torrent. Some small part of her knew that she was dreaming, but another part exulted.  <i>This is how it was meant to be. The other was a nightmare, and I have only now awakened.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup></p></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>There have always been <a href=\"/index.php/House_Targaryen\" title=\"House Targaryen\">Targaryens</a> who dreamed of things to come, since long before the <a href=\"/index.php/War_of_Conquest\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"War of Conquest\">Conquest</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Brynden_Rivers\" title=\"Brynden Rivers\">Brynden Rivers</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Duncan_the_Tall\" title=\"Duncan the Tall\">Duncan</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_V_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon V Targaryen\">Aegon Targaryen</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragon_dreams&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\" style=\"-webkit-column-width:200px; -moz-column-width:200px; column-width:200px; -webkit-column-count:2; -moz-column-count:2; column-count:2;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 11\">Chapter 11</a>, The Kraken's Daughter.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_reign_of_the_dragons:_the_conquest.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Reign of the Dragons: The Conquest.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Screenrant: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://screenrant.com/house-dragon-aegon-dream-george-rr-martin/\">Aegon's White Walkers Dream In House Of The Dragon Came From GRRM</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rthk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\">4.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Hedge_Knight\" title=\"The Hedge Knight\">The Hedge Knight</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">5.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">5.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtmk.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\">5.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Mystery_Knight\" title=\"The Mystery Knight\">The Mystery Knight</a></i>.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">6.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok6.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-1\">6.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_6\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 6\">Chapter 6</a>, Jon I.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\">7.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\">7.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-2\">7.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc26.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-3\">7.3</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_26\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 26\">Chapter 26</a>, Samwell III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_v.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/The_World_of_Ice_%26_Fire\" title=\"The World of Ice &amp; Fire\">The World of Ice &amp; Fire</a></i>, The Targaryen Kings: Aegon V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\">9.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Raffc35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-1\">9.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows\" title=\"A Feast for Crows\">A Feast for Crows</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Feast_for_Crows-Chapter_35\" title=\"A Feast for Crows-Chapter 35\">Chapter 35</a>, Samwell IV.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\">10.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot11.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-1\">10.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_11\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 11\">Chapter 11</a>, Daenerys II.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\">11.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Ragot23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\">11.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"A Game of Thrones\">A Game of Thrones</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Game_of_Thrones-Chapter_23\" title=\"A Game of Thrones-Chapter 23\">Chapter 23</a>, Daenerys III.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos23.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords\" title=\"A Storm of Swords\">A Storm of Swords</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Storm_of_Swords-Chapter_23\" title=\"A Storm of Swords-Chapter 23\">Chapter 23</a>, Daenerys II.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260403121735\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.097 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.114 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 1575/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9514/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 10246/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 3754/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 9/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 8833/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   66.366      1 -total\n 77.26%   51.275     21 Template:Ref\n 43.24%   28.697     21 Template:Ref/core\n 25.77%   17.101      7 Template:Quote\n 14.81%    9.832      1 Template:References\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key westeros_awoiaftest-mw_:pcache:idhash:10438-0!canonical and timestamp 20260403121735 and revision id 334571\n -->\n",
